1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:01,810
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,810 --> 00:00:03,510
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,510 --> 00:00:05,180
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,710 --> 00:00:07,850
(Episode 54)

5
00:00:10,180 --> 00:00:11,180
What is this?

6
00:00:14,020 --> 00:00:15,220
What do you think you're doing?

7
00:00:18,820 --> 00:00:20,160
But I feel like...

8
00:00:21,330 --> 00:00:22,790
I recognize you.

9
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:25,560
Something...

10
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:28,270
is coming back to me.

11
00:00:28,770 --> 00:00:29,770
What?

12
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,370
We know each other, don't we?

13
00:00:34,610 --> 00:00:35,610
I...

14
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:37,210
I told you, I don't.

15
00:00:38,140 --> 00:00:39,640
Yes, we do.

16
00:00:40,410 --> 00:00:42,510
I'm so close to remembering.

17
00:00:43,780 --> 00:00:44,780
I remember...

18
00:00:58,600 --> 00:00:59,600
Chloe!

19
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:01,600
Chloe.

20
00:01:20,550 --> 00:01:21,550
Chloe?

21
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:36,900
Chloe, are you okay?

22
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:41,770
What the heck did you do?

23
00:01:43,170 --> 00:01:44,540
Absolutely nothing.

24
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:46,410
This is all her.

25
00:01:46,410 --> 00:01:47,410
You!

26
00:01:50,380 --> 00:01:53,180
Chloe, let's go.
I'll take you back to your room.

27
00:02:25,180 --> 00:02:26,220
Careful.

28
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:27,750
Are you okay?

29
00:02:36,530 --> 00:02:39,100
Chloe seems to be doing worse
than Min Jun.

30
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:42,230
They said her psychological trauma
was the main issue,

31
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:45,970
but did the hit-and-run really have
that big of an impact?

32
00:02:46,770 --> 00:02:47,770
Or...

33
00:02:48,610 --> 00:02:50,910
did something else happen
at the warehouse?

34
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:54,150
What on earth happened that day?

35
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:57,280
They're still looking for Chloe.
I'd better call them.

36
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,820
You're okay now, right?

37
00:03:07,230 --> 00:03:09,030
Yes, I'm fine.

38
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:15,730
Goodness. Chloe, my gosh.

39
00:03:16,270 --> 00:03:19,440
There you are. Chloe, what happened?

40
00:03:19,970 --> 00:03:22,470
You just disappeared.
I was looking for you everywhere.

41
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:24,980
I'm sorry.

42
00:03:25,540 --> 00:03:29,280
I felt so cooped up in the room,
so I went for a walk.

43
00:03:30,050 --> 00:03:31,920
Then I suddenly got a headache.

44
00:03:31,980 --> 00:03:34,850
A headache? Why? What happened?

45
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,720
I felt like I was about
to remember something,

46
00:03:38,020 --> 00:03:39,420
so I tried to force it.

47
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:41,260
No, don't do that.

48
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:45,500
The doctor said
not to push yourself.

49
00:03:46,330 --> 00:03:49,870
I know you're frustrated,
but let's not rush things, okay?

50
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:54,210
- Okay.
- Good. Oh, dear.

51
00:03:59,110 --> 00:04:01,280
He brought me back here.

52
00:04:05,850 --> 00:04:08,990
Luckily, I was nearby,
so I was able to find her quickly.

53
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:13,690
In any case, thank you.

54
00:04:14,930 --> 00:04:16,330
Of course I should look out for her.

55
00:04:17,130 --> 00:04:18,130
Chloe is...

56
00:04:19,530 --> 00:04:20,630
my fiancee, after all.

57
00:04:35,410 --> 00:04:36,410
Chloe?

58
00:04:37,020 --> 00:04:38,020
Yes.

59
00:04:38,620 --> 00:04:40,690
There was a commotion
outside the door earlier,

60
00:04:41,290 --> 00:04:43,420
and I heard Hyun Jun
call someone Chloe.

61
00:04:43,890 --> 00:04:47,460
She's someone Hyun Jun knows.
Do I know her too?

62
00:04:48,860 --> 00:04:51,330
Should I really tell him
about Chloe?

63
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,670
That he had feelings for her,

64
00:04:54,930 --> 00:04:56,530
and that they were
in the accident together...

65
00:04:57,700 --> 00:05:00,640
What if this just brings him
more pain?

66
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:05,840
Well...

67
00:05:07,780 --> 00:05:10,010
I don't think
I've heard anything about her.

68
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:15,520
What's happening?
Is she hiding her from him?

69
00:05:16,790 --> 00:05:19,590
I think she's just someone
Hyun Jun knows personally.

70
00:05:21,190 --> 00:05:25,400
Right. I saw her out there too.
I've never seen her before.

71
00:05:30,540 --> 00:05:31,600
Chloe?

72
00:05:32,770 --> 00:05:33,970
Chloe...

73
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:36,540
The name just sounds so familiar.

74
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:37,840
It's a common name.

75
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:40,950
Is that why?

76
00:05:53,290 --> 00:05:54,530
You made the right call.

77
00:05:56,130 --> 00:05:58,860
Besides, Chloe isn't exactly
a fond memory for Min Jun.

78
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:04,100
Since you've decided, make sure
Park Hyun Jun keeps quiet too.

79
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,800
Don't get too excited.

80
00:06:06,470 --> 00:06:09,440
This was a choice I had to make
for Min Jun's sake,

81
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:12,040
but that doesn't mean
I approve of you.

82
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:17,220
You always said Min Jun's feelings
are what's most important.

83
00:06:18,150 --> 00:06:21,290
I'll stay by his side
and be mindful of his feelings.

84
00:06:21,290 --> 00:06:22,290
And of course,

85
00:06:24,420 --> 00:06:26,720
I'll do my best
to win you over too, Mother.

86
00:06:28,330 --> 00:06:29,330
Mother?

87
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:37,270
Then in return,
answer my question honestly.

88
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:41,640
What happened at the warehouse
on the day of the accident?

89
00:06:43,780 --> 00:06:44,780
What?

90
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:47,380
Don't leave anything out
and tell me the truth.

91
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:56,590
Ms. Kim, there's a huge problem.

92
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:59,190
- What is it?
- Well...

93
00:07:01,190 --> 00:07:02,190
Here.

94
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,400
We should head out right away.

95
00:07:05,730 --> 00:07:06,730
Of course.

96
00:07:10,370 --> 00:07:11,370
I wonder what that was about.

97
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:14,240
Whatever.

98
00:07:14,540 --> 00:07:16,840
At least I got out
of that awkward conversation.

99
00:07:19,410 --> 00:07:21,610
Why is she asking about
the warehouse incident again?

100
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:23,250
I thought that was all in the past.

101
00:07:27,950 --> 00:07:31,020
Director Park Min Jun's accident
is a tragedy,

102
00:07:31,820 --> 00:07:33,690
but given that he's lost his memory,

103
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:36,630
I've concluded he is unfit
to manage the company.

104
00:07:38,660 --> 00:07:40,200
Hold on.

105
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:43,470
My son just cheated death,

106
00:07:44,270 --> 00:07:45,440
and you want him to step down?

107
00:07:46,540 --> 00:07:48,970
This is all for the good
of the company.

108
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:52,310
If this news gets out,
the stock price will plummet,

109
00:07:52,810 --> 00:07:54,910
and if these family scandals
continue,

110
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:58,550
he could become a liability...

111
00:07:58,550 --> 00:07:59,580
Darn it!

112
00:08:01,020 --> 00:08:02,090
That's enough!

113
00:08:02,490 --> 00:08:05,090
I get it, all right?
Now stop talking and get out.

114
00:08:05,890 --> 00:08:07,760
What do you mean that's enough?

115
00:08:08,690 --> 00:08:12,300
The company's future is on the line.
You need to make a decision now.

116
00:08:13,430 --> 00:08:16,700
Fire Park Min Jun
and settle the matter of succession.

117
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,000
Settle it?

118
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:23,810
You can't do this, sir.

119
00:08:24,510 --> 00:08:27,210
Min Jun has only just woken up.
You can't do this to him.

120
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:31,050
Just because he's awake
doesn't mean he's okay.

121
00:08:31,380 --> 00:08:32,720
If he's reverted to being 20,

122
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,850
he's basically just a kid
without a college degree.

123
00:08:34,950 --> 00:08:37,360
How can he be an executive at Adele?

124
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:43,030
You said the successor would
be chosen through competition,

125
00:08:43,030 --> 00:08:45,060
but now he can't even qualify
as a candidate.

126
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:48,470
I'm your legal wife
and the first lady of Adele Group.

127
00:08:48,530 --> 00:08:52,700
My son can't lose to some kid
who's lost his memories. Right?

128
00:08:52,770 --> 00:08:55,740
All right, I get it.
Keep it down, will you?

129
00:08:56,210 --> 00:08:59,310
Let me think about it. Good grief.

130
00:09:13,690 --> 00:09:16,860
And whose fault is it
that Min Jun lost his memory?

131
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:19,400
You're using that as an excuse
to fire him?

132
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:22,400
Have you no conscience?

133
00:09:22,730 --> 00:09:23,940
Look who's talking.

134
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:27,440
Breaking my son's heart
was really righteous of you.

135
00:09:28,070 --> 00:09:31,540
The pain Hyun Jun went through,
and my bitter tears?

136
00:09:32,810 --> 00:09:35,780
I'll get my revenge
by taking your son's position.

137
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:39,450
I'll get what I'm owed
by taking over Adele Group.

138
00:09:39,780 --> 00:09:42,390
You ignore everything
you've done wrong...

139
00:09:43,290 --> 00:09:44,690
and just pity yourself?

140
00:09:45,990 --> 00:09:48,360
Do you have any idea
who the real victim is here?

141
00:10:19,190 --> 00:10:20,360
Come on.

142
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:24,000
I thought I told you both
to call it a day.

143
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,000
It's about Min Jun's dismissal.

144
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,770
You're not going to do it, are you?

145
00:10:28,530 --> 00:10:31,570
You made a promise 30 years ago.

146
00:10:32,070 --> 00:10:34,140
That you'd protect Min Jun and me.

147
00:10:35,270 --> 00:10:36,270
And that's why...

148
00:10:36,740 --> 00:10:40,240
That's why I'm thinking carefully.

149
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,310
Sir!

150
00:10:42,580 --> 00:10:44,620
As Min Jun's father,

151
00:10:45,350 --> 00:10:47,150
I want to protect him.

152
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:48,590
But I'm also...

153
00:10:48,650 --> 00:10:51,260
the chairman of Adele Group.

154
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:56,330
My wife isn't entirely wrong.

155
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:59,100
I should at least consider it.

156
00:10:59,930 --> 00:11:02,000
I can't just rely on Park Tae Ho.

157
00:11:02,530 --> 00:11:04,200
I need to find another way.

158
00:11:16,350 --> 00:11:18,150
Thank you, Mrs. Ok.

159
00:11:18,950 --> 00:11:22,290
Of course. I hope Chloe likes it.

160
00:11:31,830 --> 00:11:32,830
Hyun Jun.

161
00:11:33,630 --> 00:11:34,830
We should talk.

162
00:11:38,100 --> 00:11:41,070
Shouldn't you, of all people,
be on my side?

163
00:11:44,610 --> 00:11:46,440
That despicable thing I did?

164
00:11:47,140 --> 00:11:49,250
I only did it
because I was fighting to survive,

165
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:52,120
so my son wouldn't have
to live like me.

166
00:11:53,820 --> 00:11:54,950
Hold on.

167
00:11:56,020 --> 00:11:57,990
Are you saying you did that
for my sake?

168
00:11:58,390 --> 00:11:59,420
I'm saying...

169
00:12:00,460 --> 00:12:02,130
that I don't regret it.

170
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:06,330
Thanks to me, you had it all,
and now...

171
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:09,270
you're about to take over
the Adele Group.

172
00:12:12,140 --> 00:12:16,510
Hate me all you want
and refuse to forgive me.

173
00:12:17,110 --> 00:12:18,380
But for your own sake,

174
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:21,050
you have to secure your position.

175
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:25,620
It's your chance to push Min Jun out
and become the successor.

176
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:26,850
How can you...

177
00:12:29,390 --> 00:12:31,390
say something like that
at a time like this?

178
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:35,060
Because...

179
00:12:35,730 --> 00:12:37,130
I'm your mother.

180
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:40,930
No matter my past
or the situation we're in,

181
00:12:41,330 --> 00:12:43,830
my priority is securing
my son's future.

182
00:12:45,940 --> 00:12:47,710
Do you think a chance like this
comes along every day?

183
00:12:48,310 --> 00:12:52,340
You have to lock this down
while Park Min Jun has amnesia.

184
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:53,440
No.

185
00:12:54,610 --> 00:12:57,080
Whatever it is you're doing for me?

186
00:12:58,520 --> 00:12:59,780
I don't want it.

187
00:13:01,890 --> 00:13:04,420
Dealing with you is a nightmare.

188
00:13:04,420 --> 00:13:06,390
So a life you've arranged for me?

189
00:13:08,430 --> 00:13:09,660
Owning the Adele Group?

190
00:13:10,030 --> 00:13:12,000
There's no way I could handle it.

191
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:15,430
I'd rather die.

192
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:17,670
Park Hyun Jun!

193
00:13:32,450 --> 00:13:34,220
How long is he going
to keep this up?

194
00:13:34,950 --> 00:13:37,620
Can't he, of all people,
understand and overlook it?

195
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:42,130
Who does he think
I'm fighting so hard for?

196
00:13:47,870 --> 00:13:49,100
Mrs. Ok!

197
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:50,800
Yes, ma'am.

198
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:56,610
I'm upset enough as it is.
Why is this place such a mess?

199
00:13:57,010 --> 00:13:58,110
Clean it up. Now.

200
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,080
My apologies.

201
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:03,880
I've spent the whole morning
preparing two lunch boxes.

202
00:14:05,020 --> 00:14:06,020
Lunch boxes?

203
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:10,090
Mr. Hyun Jun asked me
to make lunch for Chloe.

204
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:13,390
He's so cruel to me, and yet...

205
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:16,390
The chairman also gave me an order.

206
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:20,460
He asked me to make abalone porridge
for Mr. Min Jun.

207
00:14:21,330 --> 00:14:23,530
- What?
- He said...

208
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:25,700
he was going to visit
the hospital himself,

209
00:14:25,770 --> 00:14:28,540
so I rushed to get it ready in time.

210
00:14:30,940 --> 00:14:34,550
He's even bringing
Park Min Jun porridge?

211
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:54,970
Here...

212
00:14:56,930 --> 00:14:59,940
I asked Butler Ok...

213
00:15:00,570 --> 00:15:02,010
to make this for you.

214
00:15:05,580 --> 00:15:06,580
Dig in.

215
00:15:08,350 --> 00:15:09,350
Sure.

216
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:25,160
Aren't you having any, Father?

217
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:28,770
I'm meeting someone...

218
00:15:30,870 --> 00:15:32,470
before heading to the office.

219
00:15:34,810 --> 00:15:37,410
You were always busy,
even when I was 20.

220
00:15:37,910 --> 00:15:39,680
I see that hasn't changed.

221
00:15:39,910 --> 00:15:43,150
Hey, being busy is a good thing.

222
00:15:47,820 --> 00:15:48,820
Still,

223
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:51,720
I wish we had more time like this.

224
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:56,630
Time spent with you, Father.

225
00:15:58,660 --> 00:16:00,630
I only remember things
up until I was 20,

226
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,100
but this feels new to me.

227
00:16:16,510 --> 00:16:20,080
I'll have to make sure I remember
this time we spent together.

228
00:16:20,420 --> 00:16:24,660
If I ever happen to lose my memory,
I can look back on it.

229
00:16:28,030 --> 00:16:29,630
All this time, I've been...

230
00:16:31,760 --> 00:16:33,200
strict with you.

231
00:16:35,900 --> 00:16:37,770
Min Jun, no matter what anyone says,

232
00:16:37,770 --> 00:16:39,640
you're the eldest son
of the Adele family.

233
00:16:42,170 --> 00:16:43,770
And that will never change.

234
00:16:59,860 --> 00:17:01,760
- Go on, eat up.
- Right.

235
00:17:03,730 --> 00:17:06,730
Announce
Park Min Jun's amnesia publicly.

236
00:17:07,230 --> 00:17:09,470
Claim that he has brain damage
and is mentally unfit...

237
00:17:09,470 --> 00:17:10,870
for his position.

238
00:17:11,470 --> 00:17:14,640
Use a provocative headline
and plaster it on the front page.

239
00:17:15,740 --> 00:17:18,840
What?
But the chairman told us to wait.

240
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:23,650
That's exactly why.
The chairman is taking his side.

241
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:28,090
Control the narrative with the media
so he can't change his mind.

242
00:17:28,690 --> 00:17:33,260
Corner him so he's forced to approve
the motion for dismissal.

243
00:17:37,690 --> 00:17:39,300
Jung Ran, wait.

244
00:17:39,660 --> 00:17:44,130
Isn't this a little too rushed?
You know, haste makes waste.

245
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:46,900
When things are urgent,
you have to act fast.

246
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:51,280
To be blunt, you're the one
who put Park Min Jun in this state.

247
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:53,140
That's just inhuman...

248
00:17:53,580 --> 00:17:56,580
We can worry about being humane
after this is all over,

249
00:17:56,650 --> 00:17:59,820
after Hyun Jun takes over Adele.

250
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:05,020
Stop spouting nonsense
and talk some sense into him.

251
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:06,320
Hyun Jun?

252
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:07,760
He won't talk to me,

253
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:10,290
and he'd rather die
than let me give him Adele.

254
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:13,830
So you go
and knock some sense into him.

255
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,070
No, I'm out.

256
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:26,310
Not again.
They're both driving me insane.

257
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:28,480
I need the two of them to cooperate,

258
00:18:29,350 --> 00:18:30,580
but I'm the only one trying.

259
00:18:33,150 --> 00:18:36,290
Right, Reporter Kim.
Make the headline juicier.

260
00:18:36,350 --> 00:18:39,460
Yes, that's it.
"Suffering from amnesia..." Right.

261
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:44,430
Exactly. You know the drill.
That's right, Reporter Kim.

262
00:18:49,300 --> 00:18:51,240
Director Seo?

263
00:18:55,310 --> 00:18:58,780
Hold on.
I don't care how desperate you are,

264
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:01,380
but this is incredibly rude.

265
00:19:05,180 --> 00:19:08,590
Don't you think
what you're doing is far ruder?

266
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:12,560
I'm sure you have children
of your own, Director Seo.

267
00:19:13,390 --> 00:19:17,290
If this happened to your child,
could you really stay polite?

268
00:19:20,730 --> 00:19:24,000
The chairman gave
a direct order to wait.

269
00:19:24,470 --> 00:19:28,170
Yet, you're going to defy him
and stir up trouble?

270
00:19:28,470 --> 00:19:31,170
You're planning to run a story
on Director Park's condition...

271
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:33,040
and create a media circus,

272
00:19:33,540 --> 00:19:36,210
all to pressure the chairman,
am I right?

273
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:41,690
Unless you want trouble
over your alleged dealings with Ms. Oh,

274
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:44,920
you'd better stop now.

275
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:49,560
Wait, that's...
But that's just an allegation.

276
00:19:49,630 --> 00:19:52,860
There's no proof,
and even if there were,

277
00:19:53,130 --> 00:19:54,770
Ms. Oh would handle everything.

278
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:58,440
Besides, your threats are
too little, too late.

279
00:19:58,740 --> 00:20:01,470
The articles are already out.

280
00:20:08,310 --> 00:20:09,880
Oh Jung Ran, you already...

281
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,420
The articles are already up.

282
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:19,060
(The Fall of Adele's Heir,
Dir. Park's Shocking Mental Decline)

283
00:20:28,470 --> 00:20:29,470
Here.

284
00:20:30,130 --> 00:20:31,670
You should have this, Father.

285
00:20:33,040 --> 00:20:34,040
Wait.

286
00:20:34,710 --> 00:20:37,270
Why would anyone keep this?

287
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:41,310
It's a memento. A memory.

288
00:20:46,380 --> 00:20:49,020
Sir, you need to see this.

289
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:50,890
What is it?

290
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:56,090
(The Fall of Adele's Heir,
Dir. Park's Shocking Mental Decline)

291
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:57,230
Son of a...

292
00:20:57,290 --> 00:20:59,430
(The Fall of Adele's Heir,
Dir. Park's Shocking Mental Decline)

293
00:20:59,630 --> 00:21:00,830
Is something wrong?

294
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:03,400
Here.

295
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:07,070
No, it's nothing important.

296
00:21:08,140 --> 00:21:11,940
Something urgent came up,
so I'm afraid I have to go.

297
00:21:13,580 --> 00:21:14,750
You get some rest.

298
00:21:15,610 --> 00:21:17,110
You need to rest. All right?

299
00:21:17,550 --> 00:21:20,150
- Sure.
- Right. Let's go.

300
00:21:36,830 --> 00:21:40,640
Should we put out a rebuttal article
or arrange an interview?

301
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:43,270
Most of the coverage is malicious,

302
00:21:43,270 --> 00:21:45,340
so Chairman Park is probably
feeling pressured.

303
00:21:46,180 --> 00:21:49,210
We need to take action
before the shareholders react.

304
00:21:49,580 --> 00:21:51,650
That's it. The shareholders.

305
00:21:52,620 --> 00:21:55,450
Chairman Park puts shareholders
before public opinion.

306
00:21:55,990 --> 00:21:57,790
The only way to stop the media is...

307
00:21:57,790 --> 00:21:59,960
to get support
from a major shareholder.

308
00:22:00,290 --> 00:22:03,360
I'm going to Ihwachae
to see Mrs. Han right now.

309
00:22:10,170 --> 00:22:11,400
Ta-da.

310
00:22:12,970 --> 00:22:16,370
I asked her to prepare food
that helps with cognitive recovery.

311
00:22:16,910 --> 00:22:19,180
Salmon, avocado, and walnuts.

312
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:24,650
Tomorrow, I'll ask for food
that helps reduce mental stress.

313
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:27,750
And if you want something else,
just say the word.

314
00:22:29,050 --> 00:22:33,890
Could I ask for a favor
that's not about food?

315
00:22:35,530 --> 00:22:36,530
What is it?

316
00:22:37,460 --> 00:22:38,630
What do you need?

317
00:22:48,370 --> 00:22:49,370
What's this?

318
00:22:49,740 --> 00:22:52,340
Is this why President Kim
seemed so urgent?

319
00:22:54,080 --> 00:22:56,410
Is the chairman's wife trying
to push Park Min Jun out?

320
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:01,020
Ms. Choi,

321
00:23:03,490 --> 00:23:04,490
we're with the police.

322
00:23:09,490 --> 00:23:10,490
What's this about?

323
00:23:10,630 --> 00:23:13,530
You know about the hit-and-run
at the Adele warehouse, don't you?

324
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:17,930
Were you there with Chloe,
the victim?

325
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:21,440
What?

326
00:23:21,940 --> 00:23:25,010
I can't shake the feeling
that I know you.

327
00:23:25,210 --> 00:23:27,440
I already told you we're strangers.

328
00:23:28,450 --> 00:23:29,450
That can't be right.

329
00:23:30,050 --> 00:23:32,380
I was told we know each other.

330
00:23:33,620 --> 00:23:34,620
Choi Yu Na.

331
00:23:35,550 --> 00:23:37,950
Why are you lying
when I know the truth?

332
00:23:38,390 --> 00:23:41,260
Ms. Choi. Please, cooperate with us.

333
00:23:41,560 --> 00:23:43,930
We're just trying to help Chloe
get her memory back.

334
00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:47,200
Please, just tell me
what happened that day.

335
00:23:47,460 --> 00:23:50,230
Hearing about it
might jog my memory.

336
00:23:50,930 --> 00:23:54,540
It might also help
if we shared our police statements.

337
00:23:55,140 --> 00:23:58,110
Let's all
just talk this through together.

338
00:24:02,450 --> 00:24:03,810
I have nothing to say.

339
00:24:04,550 --> 00:24:07,780
I heard you and the chairman went
to the warehouse on business,

340
00:24:08,190 --> 00:24:10,890
and I only went
because I wanted to talk to him.

341
00:24:11,990 --> 00:24:14,320
Stop bothering someone
who has nothing to do with this.

342
00:24:24,430 --> 00:24:26,270
I guess she's not going to help.

343
00:24:28,310 --> 00:24:31,610
I really thought I was on the verge
of remembering something.

344
00:24:32,810 --> 00:24:37,080
Choi Yu Na has always been strange.
Don't let her get to you.

345
00:24:40,180 --> 00:24:42,490
You had to come
all the way out here for me.

346
00:24:42,850 --> 00:24:45,060
- I'm so sorry about this.
- Not at all.

347
00:24:45,590 --> 00:24:47,820
Seeing Choi Yu Na's reaction
in person...

348
00:24:48,430 --> 00:24:51,260
makes me think we need to conduct
a full investigation of the crash.

349
00:24:52,330 --> 00:24:54,900
If you remember anything at all,
please give us a call.

350
00:24:55,170 --> 00:24:57,200
- Sure.
- We'll get going then.

351
00:24:57,330 --> 00:24:59,100
Right, thank you.

352
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:01,200
Thank you.

353
00:25:17,690 --> 00:25:18,690
What?

354
00:25:19,220 --> 00:25:21,490
Moon Tae Jin refused?

355
00:25:22,330 --> 00:25:23,330
As a shareholder of Adele,

356
00:25:23,330 --> 00:25:25,560
I thought he'd be interested
in the succession issue.

357
00:25:27,100 --> 00:25:30,330
He's definitely invested
in the succession battle.

358
00:25:30,430 --> 00:25:33,470
You're the one
he says he can't accept.

359
00:25:35,010 --> 00:25:38,110
To quote Mr. Moon directly,

360
00:25:38,510 --> 00:25:40,740
"She's not
Chairman Park Tae Ho's wife,"

361
00:25:41,010 --> 00:25:42,880
"and I refuse to discuss..."

362
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:45,950
"the succession with someone
who has no legal standing."

363
00:25:49,150 --> 00:25:50,690
This might be unpleasant to hear,

364
00:25:51,790 --> 00:25:53,690
but it's the unfortunate reality
of the situation.

365
00:25:55,230 --> 00:26:01,670
Park Min Jun was a contender before
because he's the eldest and capable.

366
00:26:02,070 --> 00:26:04,300
But now that he's lost his memory,

367
00:26:04,630 --> 00:26:06,370
it'll be difficult for him
to stay in the running.

368
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:08,440
That must be why the board...

369
00:26:08,870 --> 00:26:11,640
is pushing
to have Director Park dismissed,

370
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:13,910
and why the major shareholder
won't meet with you...

371
00:26:14,180 --> 00:26:15,950
and is backing away from everything.

372
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:36,100
I hear you even went so far
as to threaten Director Seo.

373
00:26:37,830 --> 00:26:41,940
It's useless to keep fighting.
The game is over.

374
00:26:48,810 --> 00:26:51,250
The succession war at Adele
has begun.

375
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:55,190
I have no chance if it's a fight
between the two sons.

376
00:26:58,660 --> 00:27:01,830
Oh Jung Ran and I will have
to face each other head-on.

377
00:27:02,730 --> 00:27:05,900
And I will make her pay
for trying to hurt Min Jun.

378
00:27:08,670 --> 00:27:10,500
I have to take...

379
00:27:12,140 --> 00:27:13,500
what she has.

380
00:27:31,990 --> 00:27:34,460
Ms. Kim, about dinner...

381
00:27:35,890 --> 00:27:37,660
Why are you packing all of a sudden?

382
00:27:38,260 --> 00:27:40,160
Are you leaving
on a sudden business trip?

383
00:27:40,660 --> 00:27:43,270
No. I'm leaving this house.

384
00:27:44,070 --> 00:27:45,070
What?

385
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:54,980
(Add Director Park Min Jun's dismissal
to the agenda)

386
00:28:15,300 --> 00:28:18,700
Sir, there's something
you need to see.

387
00:28:27,580 --> 00:28:28,580
What...

388
00:28:37,290 --> 00:28:39,660
What do you think you're doing?

389
00:28:42,130 --> 00:28:45,360
You're considering
dismissing Min Jun, aren't you?

390
00:28:49,570 --> 00:28:53,670
The fact that you're even struggling
with this decision means...

391
00:28:54,470 --> 00:28:55,710
leaving is the right thing to do.

392
00:28:58,510 --> 00:28:59,610
You're leaving?

393
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:01,280
I...

394
00:29:02,310 --> 00:29:04,250
moved into this house...

395
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:06,350
to protect our son.

396
00:29:06,920 --> 00:29:08,380
For Min Jun's sake,

397
00:29:09,450 --> 00:29:11,120
I've endured for the last 30 years.

398
00:29:12,490 --> 00:29:15,830
I put up with the disrespect
and humiliation.

399
00:29:19,260 --> 00:29:20,330
And yet,

400
00:29:21,630 --> 00:29:23,630
my Min Jun nearly died.

401
00:29:24,830 --> 00:29:26,600
Well, that was...

402
00:29:27,240 --> 00:29:29,140
He was in an accident.

403
00:29:29,140 --> 00:29:30,410
You don't understand, sir.

404
00:29:32,210 --> 00:29:33,740
You have no idea
how terrifying it was...

405
00:29:34,580 --> 00:29:36,080
to almost lose him.

406
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:40,250
You don't know the hopelessness...

407
00:29:41,750 --> 00:29:45,090
of being unable to protect him,
or of being unable...

408
00:29:46,590 --> 00:29:47,820
to even secure his position,

409
00:29:52,030 --> 00:29:53,030
So now,

410
00:29:54,530 --> 00:29:55,700
I'm taking Min Jun...

411
00:29:57,230 --> 00:29:58,640
and we're leaving together.

412
00:30:00,670 --> 00:30:03,970
No way. Don't be ridiculous.

413
00:30:04,040 --> 00:30:05,240
Let go of me.

414
00:30:06,140 --> 00:30:08,340
I have no reason to stay
by your side anymore.

415
00:30:09,810 --> 00:30:11,710
There's no reason?

416
00:30:12,980 --> 00:30:15,890
You have no intention
of protecting Min Jun and me.

417
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:17,750
In the end,

418
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:20,560
you're going to have
Min Jun dismissed.

419
00:30:23,560 --> 00:30:25,700
You're not even asking yourself,

420
00:30:27,260 --> 00:30:29,100
"How can I protect him?"

421
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,070
That's...

422
00:30:35,910 --> 00:30:37,210
How can I...

423
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:41,680
What is it you want me to do?

424
00:30:43,110 --> 00:30:44,950
If you want something, just tell me.

425
00:30:59,330 --> 00:31:01,600
I feel like
I'm forgetting something important.

426
00:31:03,170 --> 00:31:06,300
Is that only natural
since I've lost my memory?

427
00:31:45,710 --> 00:31:47,040
If I ask for something,

428
00:31:47,610 --> 00:31:48,610
will you do it...

429
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:50,980
no matter what?

430
00:31:51,850 --> 00:31:56,750
Yes, of course.
Just tell me what it is you want.

431
00:31:57,950 --> 00:31:58,960
Then,

432
00:32:01,020 --> 00:32:02,260
marry me.

433
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:07,500
I want to become your legal wife.

434
00:32:45,700 --> 00:32:48,740
(Pearl in Red)

435
00:32:49,010 --> 00:32:51,840
Chloe... Why am I bothered by her?

436
00:32:51,840 --> 00:32:53,440
Did she really lose her memory?

437
00:32:53,580 --> 00:32:54,710
What if she's lying?

438
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:57,410
From your children
to your positions,

439
00:32:57,710 --> 00:32:59,150
I'm the one who decides everything.

440
00:32:59,150 --> 00:33:02,790
Don't get arrogant
and step out of line again.

441
00:33:02,950 --> 00:33:05,790
From the day my sister died
until now,

442
00:33:05,860 --> 00:33:08,260
Mr. Song has always been
by Oh Jung Ran's side.

443
00:33:08,420 --> 00:33:10,930
I need to do some digging on him.

444
00:33:11,130 --> 00:33:13,600
Look into his history
with Oh Jung Ran.

445
00:33:14,300 --> 00:33:16,300
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
